name: Mick Barr - Coiled Malescence CD
description:
Brand new studio album by avant-garde metal composer/guitar genius Mick Barr (of Orthrelm, Krallice, The Flying Luttenbachers, etc...).
Coiled Malescence is a long non-repetitive piece for solo guitar, comprised of seven distinct parts/movements. This is Mick's first solo release under his own name, and probably one of his most intricate and challenging pieces of music.
In addition to the epic 35 + min title track, the CD includes 2 bonus multi-layered guitar pieces from the unreleased Intrinsic Striations EP.
Total time = 60 minutes.

name: The Scissor Girls - SG DVD
description:
Here's a lesson in how to make a music DVD!
More than two hours of live performances, promo videos and tv appearances, all assembled into a cohesive, chronological movie.
This is THE ultimate Scissor Girls documentary!

Directed by band member/mutimedia artist Kelly Kuvo, and originally released in a very limited edition of 30 homemade copies in 2004, the DVD covers the band's career from 1993 to 1996, and includes, among other things, the entirety of the SG Research videos.

The Scissor Girls were one of the best bands to emerge from the Chicago scene of the early '90s, and their unique brand of psychedelic new wave is still way ahead of its time some fifteen years later. 
This is your chance to finally own these videos, which are a major part of the band's legacy.

name: Sheik Anorak/Mario Rechtern/Weasel Walter LP
description:
Limited vinyl-only release from the improv trio that's been setting Europe on fire. 

The band, often (mistakenly) referred to as the Weasel Walter Trio, has been touring Europe relentlessly for the past three years, perfecting their sound with each new show, and reaching new heights of weirdness and intensity with every new tour.

The bizarre combination of Weasel's special brand of slapstick/free jazz/death metal drumming with Mario Rechtern's hyper-expressive skronk and Sheik Anorak's psychedelic "noise rock" background also take the "genre is obsolete" moto to a new level.
You'd never thought music this original and intense was possible in 2010.

This album has been carefully edited from hours of live recordings from their april 2010 tour of Scandinavia, Germany and Benelux, and can be considered a "best of" of some kind.
It's limited to 200 copies (almost half of which are already gone!) on clear vinyl with deluxe transparent cover.

name: Barr-Nevai - «Labyrintha» CD
description: BARR-NEVAI is a neoclassical extreme metal duo that specialize in long-duration space-rock journeys that differ slightly in style from album to album. They are known for their hypertechnical "bionic" form and lightspeed improvisation with glossolalic lyrics sung in a creepily religious-sounding unison or bowel-shudderingly-throatsung. Metrically complex, they exhibit an uncanny formal continuity that Nevai claims is "telepathik". Their musicological agenda is to "advance yet consolidate" biomechanical extreme metal by innovating it's athletic and virtuostic aspects while galvanizing it's contrapuntal and harmonic ones.

name: _ - Exekutioner's Extinktion CD
description:
Black Metal meets Classical meets Jazz improv, at the hands of the South Florida Noise scene. 
Featuring members of Harry Pussy and To Live and Shave in L.A.

personnel:
Rat Bastard - violin
Dan Hosker - cello
Nondor Nevai - drums + vocals

Exekutioner's Extinktion compiles everything the band has ever recorded. (well... minus the now-banned DMT Rok album)
It includes the 1st 2 demos (including the colossal Sonata for _), a brand new 16 min studio track and a bunch of extras from the 2nd demo sessions.

7 studio tracks total,
engineered by Rat Bastard (aka the King of Noise) @ L.R.M.B.
total running time: 52 minutes

name: 16-17 - 16-17 / When All Else Fails... 2xCD
description:
Long-awaited double-CD reissue of the 1st 3 releases by Swiss punk-jazz pioneers 16-17 .

	This collection documents the first incarnation of the band, which consisted of Alex Buess (Ice, God, Cortex) on sax, Markus Kneubühler on guitar and electronics, and Nicolas Knut Remond (Voice Crack) on drums.

	It includes the 1st 2 albums (16-17 from 1986 and When All Else Fails from 1989) and the very limited cassette-only Hardkore & Buffbunker EP from 1984, all freshly remastered by specialist Weasel Walter.

	18 tracks of pure fury, that will certainly appeal to fans of God, Painkiller, Borbetomagus, The Flying Luttenbachers, etc…

name: 16-17 - Gyatso CD
description:
After being out-of-print for almost 10 years, 16-17’s studio masterpiece from 1994 is finally available again.

	Produced by Kevin Martin (God, Ice, Techno Animal) and featuring G.C. Green of Godflesh on bass,
‘Gyatso’ is best described as an experimental studio deconstruction work based on live recordings by the original line-up of the band.
(Alex Buess, Markus Kneubühler, Knut Remond)
Today, it still stands as 16-17’s most ambitious album and a landmark in extreme rock/jazz.

	This reissue features new artwork and very detailed liner notes, and was remastered for maximum efficiency by Weasel Walter. (The Flying Luttenbachers)

name: To Live and Shave in L.A. - Les Tricoteuses CD
description:
Technically a 2007 “radical noise-dub reconfiguration” of the (rushed) Interview With the Mitchell Brothers album, Les Tricoteuses can be considered the missing link between the aforementioned album and the Wigmaker.
(the visceral passion of the former + the intricate post-production of the latter)

	Running time: 73 minutes

	Personnel:
Tom Smith
Rat Bastard
Ben Wolcott
Billy Taylor
	Artwork by Gregory Jacobsen.

artists.name: To Live and Shave in L.A.

name: Weasel Walter - Early Recordings 1988-1991 CD
description: Notorious multi-instrumentalist, improviser and composer Weasel Walter is best known for his violent drumming in the long-running punk/jazz group the Flying Luttenbachers in addition to his activity in scores of other notable bands such as Lake Of Dracula, XBXRX, Bobby Conn, Erase Errata, Lair of the Minotaur and To Live and Shave in L.A. Since the formation of the Luttenbachers in late 1991, Walter has carved away at defining a very singular aesthetic – one that focuses on apocalyptic energy, harmonic dissonance and a general sense of the unexpected. Inspired as a teenager by equal parts punk rock, free jazz, no wave, Xenakis, Captain Beefheart and more, Walter set about performing and recording his own bizarre fusion with just a gaggle of instruments, a vivid imagination and a cassette four-track. This release distills the most coherent and brilliant peformances down from more than a dozen hours of tape into almost 80 minutes of fast-moving and inspired experimentalism ranging from extended compositions to succinct improvisations. Guitars skronk, drums bash, bass clarinets and saxophones mingle with primitive electronics in a multitude of forms and combinations.

name: Lake Of Dracula - Skeletal Remains CD
description: Between 1995 and 1997 Lake Of Dracula forged a singular approach to dissonant, minimalistic rock music pre-dating both the neo-”no wave” nostalgia trip (popularized by bands like Yeah Yeah Yeahs and Liars) and the current noise rock insurgence (led by Lightning Bolt and Wolf Eyes) by years. based in Chicago, LOD was a veritable midwestern underground supergroup featuring James “Marlon” Magas (Couch, Magas), Weasel Walter (The Flying Luttenbachers, XBXRX), Heather M. (The Scissor Girls), “The Manhattanite” (a.k.a. Al Johnson from U.S. Maple) and Jessica Ruffins (Jaks, Sea of Tombs). “Skeletal Remains” collects previously unreleased material and rare compilation and single tracks onto one CD (remastered by Weasel Walter) with extensive liner notes and photos.

name: Nondor Nevai - The Wooden Machine Music CD
description: Bizarre modern compositions for player piano by the notorious cult musician Nondor Nevai! An overload of notes cascading and careening in and out of fields of total madness!

name: Group: Xex CD
description: Xex were an astonishing anomaly. A mélange of Eastern & Central European parentage, the group combined arch socio-political commentary with an equally incisive, audacious electro-pop sensibility, an alien aesthetic which fused in the otherwise torpid cultural kiln of mid-century suburban New Jersey. No MIDI, no PCs, no polyphonic synthesizers, no click tracks, all live, all in real time. And amazing, breathtaking songs, performed with a droll insouciance that makes Fred Schneider seem like Alan Greenspan by comparison. group: xex is the deal-breaker, droogs. Now is your time to pounce!

name: Kevin Drumm CD
description:
Mr. Drumm's amazing 1st album, released in 1996 on the wonderful Perdition Plastics imprint of Chicago.

Probably one of the best table-top guitar albums you'll ever hear... except it never sounds like guitar at all. 
This is noise, musique concrete, modern composition, minimalism, and whatever you want it to be. 
A perfect balance of harshness, near silence, microphone abuse and droney electronic musical landscapes. 
A true landmark in experimental music. 

Note: This is the original pressing, not the 2010 reissue. The sound is exactly the same, but the artwork looks better.
